Also on this day:

In 1807, as a war measure against French Emperor Napoleon
Bonaparte, the British announced a blockade of Continental
Europe.

In 1785 Frenchman Jean-Pierre Blanchard and American Dr. John
Jeffries became the first men to cross the English Channel in a
balloon. It was filled with hydrogen.

