Yesterday's question and answer:

This was a hard one and I received every answer imaginable. Maybe
I should have given you a few more hints. The question was
"Senator Robert Taft compared lending military equipment to this
substance." The substance is chewing gum, because "once you lend
it you don't want it back." Mike Calkins sent me the answer
first.

